

=Description=

"Foundation-owned companies are nonprofit institutions that combine business ownership and philanthropy. The foundation has a duty to ensure that the strategy of the company is inline with its statutes. 

There are a range of models for foundation ownership; many optimize for tax purposes or ensuring that wealth stays within borders, while others intend to keep the operations of a firm in line with a particular set of values."

(https://cip.org/research/ci-corporation)


